cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper discusses device-to-device (D2D) communication in cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves power control and mode selection, which are related to information theory and system design, respectively. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of D2D communication on network performance, which is related to multimedia and security. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also possible categories.
